folders.title: KINGDOM
folders.description:
Sermon on the Mount
The Radical Minimum Standards of Christianity are the baseline of what is expected as followers of Jesus.

folders.title: R E B E L
folders.description: An altered perspective

folders.title: A Defining DNA
folders.description: There are 3 Distinct DNA Markers that distinguish and define every follower of Jesus and every Church.

folders.title: UNKNOWN
folders.description: We are looking at unknown factors in the Bible that had massive ramifications for what we are still talking about thousands of years later.

folders.title: Psalm 23
folders.description: Join us as we take part in a study of Psalm 23 and the comfort that Jesus brings as our Shepherd.

folders.title: VOICE
folders.description: The purpose of this series is to answer the question does God speak? How does He speak? How do I know when He is Speaking to Me? What do I do to when He speaks?

folders.title: Warfare
folders.description:
"For we do not wrestle against flesh and blood, but against the rulers, against the authorities, against the cosmic powers over this present darkness, against the spiritual forces of evil in the heavenly places." Ephesians 6:12  
As believers we DO NOT live in fear, but instead we are called to stand firm.

folders.title: Prodigal
folders.description: Join us as we study the parable of the Prodigal Son. We look to the three main characters the son, the father, and the brother to see their perspectives in this story of rebellion and redemption.

folders.title: Famous: Stories from the Bible
folders.description: Join us as we examine popular stories from the Bible that are often taught at a young age and how those lessons have great implications for us still.

folders.title: The Book of Judges
folders.description: The book of Judges has many incredible stories of God's deliverance of His people in the Old Testament.                                                                                                          Join us as we examine a few of these incredible stories of the men and women God raised up to lead His people.

folders.title: Freedom Weekend
folders.description:
Galatians 5:1  For freedom Christ has set us free; stand firm therefore, and do not submit again to a yoke of slavery.
We hear the stories of two U.S. servicemen PO1 Tyson Schmidt, U.S. Navy and SSG Daniel Gilland, U.S. Army. They describe their struggle after tragic injuries and their redemption in Jesus Christ.

folders.title: Ruth
folders.description: There is prodigal in all of us.  The desire to know for ourselves what many have warned us against is the propensity within us all.  Many have gone before us, warning us, steering us away from the distant country of regrets and remorse, but the draw is magnetic.  Unfortunately, the only aspects that seem to adhere are the unfortunate mishaps and mistakes that label you and shame you.  The story of Ruth is one of Return, Reconciliation, and Restoration.

folders.title: Winsome
folders.description: Often times, we begin with the fear, what do I say, but this series is not so much built on what you say, but how you live.  THUS OUR ENTIRE SERIES CALLED WINSOME!

folders.title: More Than Words
folders.description:
For the next seven weeks we will listen, learn and lean into
the final words of Jesus upon the cross, seeking to understand why He chose these seven statements,
what did they mean in context, and how do they lead us to respond today.

folders.title: 21 Days: Praying and Fasting for the Harvest
The Passion and Pursuit
folders.description: Join us this summer as we take an in depth look into the life of King David.  From his victorious exploits as a ruddy youth to the legacy he passed down through generations. David was passionate in all of his pursuits causing him to be called a "man after God's own heart."

folders.title: Guest Speaker: Brent Crowe, Ph.D.
folders.description:
We study Jesus' conversation on the cross with the criminal next to Him, which gives us a beautiful example of His grace.  

"Then one of the criminals who were hanged blasphemed Him, saying, 'If You are the Christ, save Yourself and us.'
But the other, answering, rebuked him, saying, 'Do you not even fear God, seeing you are under the same condemnation? 
And we indeed justly, for we receive the due reward of our deeds; but this Man has done nothing wrong.'
Then he said to Jesus, 'Lord, remember me when You come into Your kingdom.'
And Jesus said to him, 'Assuredly, I say to you, today you will be with Me in Paradise.'"
Luke 23: 39-43.

folders.title: Radical
folders.description: The perception of an individual's significance is usually without the filter of a backstory of the investment of those in the background. Therefore, your legacy as a person of significant influence is not only defined by the tangible qualities you possess, but also the intangible qualities you deposit.

folders.title: How to Get God's Blessing in Your Home
folders.description: We've all heard athletes, actors, couples, and successful people thank the Lord for blessing their lives. How do we get Gods blessings in our home?

folders.title: I Am
folders.description:
You are the workmanship of God, created for Him to give glory to Him by living through Him. The greatest challenge to a life of higher calling is a failure to understand who the One is doing the calling. Therefore, to live life with meaning, magnitude, and great measure, I must allow my limitations of
what "I am not" to be transformed by the "I AM".

folders.title: Get With The Good Shepherd
folders.description: Jason Cook played collegiate football at The University of Mississippi (Ole Miss) where he would be a 4 year starter and 4 year letter winner at Fullback. In 2009, Jason enjoyed a brief stint with the Baltimore Ravens through the pre-season before embracing the call to ministry.  Jason holds a Masters of Divinity from Beeson Divinity School in Birmingham, Alabama.  Jason and his wife Courtney, have two children Charlie and Cager. Together they serve as the Associate Pastor of Preaching at Fellowship Memphis and as the editor with the Gospel Coalition contributing to the Faith and Work initiative.

folders.title: 40 Days
folders.description: 40 days of prayer and fasting with Dr. Ed Newton

folders.title: Greatest Love Story Ever
folders.description: "Advent" means "coming" or "arrival." Learn how prepare for the arrival of Jesus Christ as we celebrate His birth and Second Coming.

folders.title: The Holy Spirit
folders.description: Discover the foundation principles of the Holy Spirit.

folders.title: Family Talk
folders.description: Getting' real where it really matters.

folders.title: A Message for Mom
folders.description: A time of blessing for mothers here and around the world.

folders.title: This I Believe
folders.description: Studying the eye-opening moments where people have said "This I Believe".

folders.title: The Seven
folders.description: Looking at the seven churches of Asia and how they prophetically, practically, pragmatically and personally relate to us as individuals.
